      "message": "There is always a 1:1 mapping between postFrame() and onSocketEvent(), I think the real reason is that QEMU2 is more heavily multi-threaded and probably uses more signals, this implies that  the socketRecv() may sometimes return with an error like EINTR or EAGAIN, i.e. nothing is recv()-ed at all.\n\nThe check for !c seems ok given the circumstances, but it\u0027s probably a little cleaner to check that socketRecv() returns +1, i.e. that a byte has indeed been read from the socket.\n\nAnyway, thanks for finding this!",
